1.title: Fall in the Family
1.plot: In its most competitive season to date, "Wipeout" returns with a super-sized family edition, featuring teams of two family members enduring another true bonding (and bruising) experience. Only the remaining two teams will take a family trip to the all-new Wipeout Zone for a chance to win the grand prize and earn a spot in the first ever "Tournament of Champions" at the end of the summer.

2.title: Hotties vs. Nerds 4.0
2.plot: Tape up your glasses and spray on your tan, our fourth annual edition of Hotties vs. Nerds on "Wipeout" is back again with 12 new hotties and 12 new nerds. These 24 contestants including, "Nordic Beauty," "Sir Jock or Not" and "3-D Prince" will be dining at the "Robo-Bistro" and taking a trip to the outer orbit on "Space Race." Our top 4 contestants will move on to face the Wipeout Zone, but only 1 will walk away with the cash prize and a spot to compete in the epic "Tournament of Champions" battle at the end of the season.

3.title: All-American Wipeout
3.plot: Wipeout celebrates America with its very own amber waves of pain. The qualifier round will kick off as they conquer the Space Race, but only 6 contestants will be able to move on with a seat at the Thanksgiving dinner table. The top four to survive will be stuffed with a ticket to the Wipeout Zone, hoping to earn a big stack of All-American cash and a spot in the Tournament of Champions at the end of the season.

4.title: Win a Date with Jill
4.plot: Suit up for our first-ever edition of "Win A Date with Jill." These 24 charming bachelors will do their best to impress our lovely co-host, Jill Wagner, as they showcase their dynamite personalities while tackling the world's toughest obstacle course. The contestants will prove whether or not they are boyfriend material before they face Jill's bodyguard "The Classic Sweeper." Only 1 will be lucky enough to score the cash prize, a solo date with Jill and a spot to compete in the "Tournament of Champions" at the end of the season.

5.title: Flush Hour
5.plot: 24 brand new contestants face the ultimate athletic challenge for the average man. First up, our contestants will take on the challenging Qualifier where they will rush to make it to the bathroom and choose a door at the "The Johns," before hitting the World Famous Big Balls. Moving on, the contestants fight to finish the Space Race before battling Fun Slides plat-formed Spinning Purple People Beater. The remaining four contestants will have a blast in the Wipeout Zone but only one contestant will run home with a massive stash of cash.

6.title: Blind Date: Falling for You
6.plot: Contestants compete on an extreme obstacle course for a $50,000 prize.

7.title: Bachelors vs. Bachelorettes
7.plot: Fall head over heels in a new way with our exciting "Bachelors vs. Bachelorettes" edition of "Wipeout" as former "The Bachelor" and "The Bachelorette" contestants compete in a new physical challenge. The contestants hope to make a real splash as they face The Beaver and Beaverettes, The Big Balls and Gym Class along their quest to win a big cash prize. Our competitors include Erica Rose, Tenley Molzahn, Michelle Kujawa, Arie Luyendyk, Graham Bunn, Kasey Stewart and Natalie Getz, but only one will earn the money and a ticket to the "Tournament of Champions" battle at ...

8.title: Wide World of Wipeout
8.plot: Shiver me timbers! Join us as a rare breed of athletes make their mark on the "Wipeout" course. Get ready and watch the competition unfold aboard the S.S. Booty Shaker and the classic Big Balls. 24 ballsy contestants including "Beard Braid" and "Indiana Josh" trek through muck and water along their journey to the rich cash prize and a spot to compete in the "Tournament of Champions" at the end of the season.

9.title: Exes and OHH's!
9.plot: Ex marks the splat, as 12 teams of ex-couples including "Hot Pants and The Heartbreaker," "Dempsey and The Sister Kisser" and "Extra Baggage," put on their gloves and square off against the "Wipeout" course. Catch all the awkward moments as these former couples team up to take on the Mayan Ruins, Play Pound and even hash out some issues during their visit to the Divorce Court.

10.title: Boss & Employee: Big Balls, Inc.
10.plot: Bosses and employees team up to tackle the obstacle course.

11.title: My So-Bald Life
11.plot: Host John Henson may have lost all of his hair, but 24 new contestants compete on hair-raising obstacles for the big money prize. Our contestants, including "Big Foot Enthusiast" and "Paid to Party," tan their hides at "Wipeout Shores" and swing by "Dracula's Condo" for a scary good time. But only one will snatch the cash prize.

12.title: Fraternity vs. Sorority; Tournament of Champions
12.plot: Season 7 ends with fraternities and sororities engaging in battle, and previous winners returning in a tournament of champions.
